The paper deals with multi-agent path planning, which is a problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). The algorithm presented in the paper is designed to be scalable and has low-polynomial worst-case upper bounds, which suggests that it may be related to data structures (cs.DS) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the completeness of the algorithm with respect to different subclasses of instances, which suggests that it may be related to programming languages (cs.PL).
